    UriPatternDelegate

    public abstract class AbstractUriPatternDelegate
extends com.poesys.bs.delegate.AbstractDataDelegate<BsUriPattern,IUriPattern,com.poesys.db.pk.SequencePrimaryKey>

    A business delegate that provides an application programming interface for UriPattern objects and their dependents. You should not modify this class; instead, override or add methods in the class UriPatternDelegate, which specializes this class.

    A regular expression pattern that specifies a set of URIs

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
    See Also:
    UriPatternDelegate

      • createUriPattern

        public BsUriPattern createUriPattern(java.math.BigInteger uriPatternId,
                            java.lang.String pattern)
                              throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException

        Create a new UriPattern with data fields.

        The UriPattern class has a sequence key; this method generates the sequence for later insertion into the database.

        Parameters:
        uriPatternId - primary key attribute
        pattern - a regular expression that identifies a set of URIs
        Returns:
        the new UriPattern object
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when there is a problem generating the key or creating the object
